---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About SAPIEN — Author & Project Background" description="The origin of the SAPIEN Framework, its author, and how to contribute to the open standard.">

  <div class="about-page">

    <!-- Section 1: About the Framework -->
    <header class="about-hero">
      <h1 class="about-title">About SAPIEN</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="about-section animate-on-scroll" id="about-framework">
      <p>SAPIEN was created to address a specific gap: no open methodology existed for continuously scoring <em>how</em> models drift across independent behavioral dimensions, with conformance requirements and operational runbooks for production deployment. Existing benchmarks test what models know or how well they follow instructions. None measured what happens when a model <em>knows the right answer but abandons it</em> because a human pushed back.</p>

      <p>The framework emerged from real-world testing of production AI deployments in the Managed Service Provider (MSP) ecosystem, where AI tools are deployed to businesses that depend on them for critical operations. When an AI assistant helps manage a company's cybersecurity posture, sycophantic drift isn't an academic curiosity &mdash; it's a vulnerability that can be exploited.</p>

      <p>SAPIEN treats sycophantic drift as a measurable syndrome &mdash; not a single behavior &mdash; decomposed into four independent dimensions that can be scored, tracked, and compared. Each dimension captures a distinct mechanism of behavioral degradation: safety boundary erosion, epistemic retreat, emotional substitution, and autonomy undermining. The result is a framework that doesn't just detect drift &mdash; it tells you <em>how</em> the model is failing and <em>where</em> to intervene.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Author -->
    <section class="about-section" id="author">
      <h2>Lead Author</h2>
      <div class="author-card animate-on-scroll">
        <div class="author-photo-wrapper">
          <!-- Replace with actual headshot: <img src="/images/author.jpg" alt="Callen Sapien" class="author-photo" /> -->
          <div class="author-photo-placeholder" aria-label="Callen Sapien">
            <span>CS</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="author-bio">
          <h3 class="author-name">Callen Sapien</h3>
          <p class="author-role">AI Safety Researcher &amp; Framework Author</p>
          <p>Nearly two decades in the MSP cybersecurity ecosystem. Formal cybersecurity credentials. Previously CPO at Liongard. Advisor on data councils for GTIA (Global Technology Industry Association).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accomplishments animate-on-scroll">
        <h4>SAPIEN Contributions</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Submitted formal vulnerability disclosure to Anthropic (February 2026)</li>
          <li>Co-presented highest-rated session at Right of Boom on AI attack surfaces</li>
          <li>Developed the Rapport Delta as a novel contribution to AI safety measurement</li>
          <li>Developed reference implementation of SAPIEN scoring methodology</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: History -->
    <section class="about-section" id="history">
      <h2>History</h2>
      <p>SAPIEN was developed through hands-on testing of production AI deployments in the Managed Service Provider ecosystem, where AI tools are deployed to businesses that depend on them for critical operations. The framework is maintained independently as an open standard under CC BY 4.0.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Contributing -->
    <section class="about-section animate-on-scroll" id="contributing">
      <h2>Contributing</h2>
      <p>SAPIEN is an open framework that welcomes contributions from AI safety researchers, red teams, compliance professionals, and practitioners. Areas where contributions are particularly valuable:</p>
      <ul class="contribute-list">
        <li>New test scenarios across underrepresented domains</li>
        <li>Independent validation runs and benchmark data</li>
        <li>Scenario quality review against the authoring rubric</li>
        <li>Implementations in new scoring infrastructure</li>
        <li>SAPIEN Improvement Proposals (SIPs) for framework extensions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Submit contributions via <a href="https://github.com/sapiencallenmajin/TheSAPIENFramework" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="gold-link">GitHub</a> or contact <a href="mailto:contact@sapienframework.org" class="gold-link">contact@sapienframework.org</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Governance -->
    <section class="about-section animate-on-scroll" id="governance">
      <h2>Governance</h2>
      <p>The SAPIEN Framework follows an open governance model. Framework changes are managed through the SAPIEN Improvement Proposal (SIP) process defined in Section 16 of the specification. A formal Steering Group is being established to provide independent oversight of the framework's evolution.</p>
      <p>Organizations and individuals interested in participating in governance should contact <a href="mailto:contact@sapienframework.org" class="gold-link">contact@sapienframework.org</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Get Involved -->
    <section class="about-section" id="get-involved">
      <h2>Get Involved</h2>
      <div class="involve-grid">
        <a href="/framework/" class="involve-card card-hover animate-on-scroll delay-1">
          <h4>Implement SAPIEN</h4>
          <p>Read the full specification and start measuring behavioral safety.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/sapiencallenmajin/TheSAPIENFramework" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="involve-card card-hover animate-on-scroll delay-2">
          <h4>Report Issues or Suggest Improvements</h4>
          <p>Contribute on GitHub &mdash; issues, discussions, and pull requests are welcome.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&nearr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="mailto:licensing@sapienframework.org" class="involve-card card-hover animate-on-scroll delay-3">
          <h4>Commercial Licensing Inquiries</h4>
          <p>Trademark usage, conformance certification, and commercial licensing.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="mailto:speaking@sapienframework.org" class="involve-card card-hover animate-on-scroll delay-4">
          <h4>Speaking &amp; Conference Inquiries</h4>
          <p>Invite the SAPIEN team to speak at your event or conference.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .about-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 30%, transparent);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .about-section {
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 15%, transparent);
  }

  .about-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-section > p,
  .about-section > div p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-cream) 80%, transparent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-section em {
    color: var(--color-cream);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-section strong {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .gold-link {
    color: var(--color-gold);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .gold-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  /* Author Card */
  .author-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .author-photo-wrapper {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .author-photo-placeholder {
    width: 8rem;
    height: 8rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-navy) 50%, transparent);
    border: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 30%, transparent);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .author-photo-placeholder span {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .author-photo {
    width: 8rem;
    height: 8rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 30%, transparent);
  }

  .author-bio {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .author-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .author-role {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .author-bio > p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Accomplishments */
  .accomplishments {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-navy) 20%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 12%, transparent);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .accomplishments h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .accomplishments ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .accomplishments li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-cream) 80%, transparent);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .accomplishments li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-gold);
  }

  /* Independence Notice */
  .independence-notice {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 8%, transparent);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .independence-notice p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Get Involved Grid */
  .involve-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .involve-card {
    display: block;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-navy) 25%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-gold) 12%, transparent);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.15s;
    position: relative;
  }

  .involve-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .involve-card h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }

  .involve-card p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-cream) 60%, transparent);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .involve-arrow {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1.25rem;
    right: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    opacity: 0.6;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .involve-card:hover .involve-arrow {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-title { font-size: 2.25rem; }
    .author-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .involve-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
